data.Name: Measured Depth
data.Description: Measured depth along the wellbore with zero reference point given by WellboreTrajectory data.VerticalMeasurement.

data.Name: Inclination
data.Description: Hole inclination, measured from vertical.

data.Name: Azimuth True North
data.Description: True North hole azimuth. Corrected to True North azimuth reference.

data.Name: Azimuth Grid North
data.Description: Grid North referenced hole azimuth measurement. The 'grid' is defined by WellboreTrajectory data.ProjectedCRSID.

data.Name: Azimuth Magnetic North
data.Description: Magnetic North referenced hole azimuth measurement.

data.Name: Displacement East-West
data.Description: East-West offset, positive to the East. This is relative to well location with a North axis orientation given by WellboreTrajectory data.ProjectedCRSID.

data.Name: Displacement North-South
data.Description: North-South offset, positive to the North. This is relative to well location with a North axis orientation given by WellboreTrajectory data.ProjectedCRSID.

data.Name: True Displacement East-West
data.Description: True East-West offset, positive to the East. This is relative to well location with a North axis orientation given by the geographic CRS's North using an azimuthal equidistant projection at the wellbore location.

data.Name: True Displacement North-South
data.Description: North-South offset, positive to the North. This is relative to well location with a North axis orientation given by the geographic CRS's North using an azimuthal equidistant projection at the wellbore location.

data.Name: WGS 84 Longitude
data.Description: World map longitude based on WGS 84 (EPSG:4326).

data.Name: WGS 84 Latitude
data.Description: World map latitude based on WGS 84 (EPSG:4326).

data.Name: True Vertical Depth
data.Description: True vertical depth with zero reference point given by WellboreTrajectory data.VerticalMeasurement.

data.Name: True Vertical Depth Sub Sea
data.Description: True vertical depth with zero reference point given by Mean Sea Level (MSL)

data.Name: Dogleg Severity
data.Description: The wellbore curvature. In surveying wellbore trajectories, a standard calculation of dogleg severity is made, usually expressed in two-dimensional degrees per 100 feet or degrees per 30 m of wellbore length.

data.Name: IsOriginal
data.Description: Boolean flag indicating a sample belonging to a measured, original trajectory station. False (0) indicates interpolated samples.

data.Name: Station ID
data.Description: Unique identifier of survey station within the directional survey.

data.Name: Radius of Uncertainty
data.Description: The radius of uncertainty distance of this survey station

data.Name: Easting
data.Description: The easting value of the point in the directional survey. Local CRS must be defined.

data.Name: Northing
data.Description: The northing value of the point in the directional survey. Local CRS must be defined.

data.Name: Delta Latitude
data.Description: The difference between the well surface hole latitude and the survey station latitude. A positive value indicates a northerly direction; a negative value indicates a southerly direction.  ADD this value to the well Surface Latitude to define the Station Latitude.

data.Name: Delta Longitude
data.Description: The difference between the well surface hole longitude and the survey station longitude. A positive value indicates an easterly direction; a negative value indicates a westerly direction.  ADD this value to the well Surface Longitude to define the Station Longitude.

data.Name: Original Latitude
data.Description: The latitude of the station in the directional survey.  Recommended practice is to utilize DELTA LAT and DELTA LONG instead of storing actual LATITUDE/LONGITUDE values. NOTE - If the LATITUDE/LONGITUDE attributes are populated, the Geodetic Datum must be defined in the record.

data.Name: Original Longitude
data.Description: The longitude value of the point in the directional survey.  Recommended practice is to utilize DELTA LAT and DELTA LONG instead of storing actual LATITUDE/LONGITUDE values. NOTE - If the LATITUDE/LONGITUDE attributes are populated, the Geodetic Datum must be defined in the record.

data.Name: Closure Distance (True North)
data.Description: The horizontal straight line distance from the survey origin 0,0,0) to this survey station, calculated using the Pythagorean Theorem from this survey station X and Y Offsets.  The distance is computed in a local CRS with scale factor one.  Often referred to as simply "True Closure" or sometimes referred to as "True Horizontal Displacement".

data.Name: Closure Distance (Projected)
data.Description: The horizontal straight line distance from the survey origin (Well surface location) to this survey station, calculated using the Pythagorean Theorem from this survey station X and Y Offsets.  Closure Distance is often reported only once for the bottom hole location; however, the value stored in this attribute is the Closure Distance at this survey station.  The distance is subject to distortions by the projection, in which the closure is computed.  Often referred to as simply "Closure" or sometimes referred to as "Horizontal Displacement".

data.Name: Closure Distance Direction (True North)
data.Description: The direction angle between survey origin and this survey station, calculated using trigonometry from this survey station X and Y Offsets. The direction is calculated in a True North oriented, local coordinate reference system anchored at the survey origin (Well surface location).  This value should be a number between 0.00 and 360.00 degrees; 0.00 and 360.00 represent North, 90.00 is East, 180.00 is South and 270.00 is West.

data.Name: Closure Distance Direction (Projected)
data.Description: The direction angle, in the horizontal plane, from the survey origin (Well surface location) to this survey station, calculated using trigonometry from this survey station X and Y Offsets.  This value should be a number between 0.00 and 360.00 degrees; 0.00 and 360.00 represent North, 90.00 is East, 180.00 is South and 270.00 is West.  The Closure Distance Direction angle North Reference is defined by WELL DIR SURVEY.OFFSET NORTH TYPE and CRS by WELL DIR SURVEY.OFFSET COORD SYSTEM ID.  Sometimes referred to as "Horizontal Displacement Direction" or "Horizontal Displacement Bearing".

data.Name: Elevation from MSL
data.Description: The elevation measured from mean sea level, the negative of TVDSS.

data.Name: WGS 84 Delta Latitude
data.Description: The difference between the well surface hole latitude and the survey station latitude, both based on WGS 84 EPSG 4326. A positive value indicates a northerly direction; a negative value indicates a southerly direction.  ADD this value to the well Surface Latitude WGS 84 to define the Station Latitude WGS 84.

data.Name: WGS 84 Delta Longitude
data.Description: The difference between the well surface hole longitude and the survey station longitude, both based on WGS 84, EPSG 4326. A positive value indicates an easterly direction; a negative value indicates a westerly direction.  ADD this value to the well Surface Longitude WGS 84 to define the Station Longitude WGS 84.

data.Name: Vertical Section
data.Description: As seen from a Plan View plot, the vertical section length from Vertical Section Origin e.g. Well Origin, to projected point of Survey station along the vertical plane defined by the vertical section azimuth.

data.Name: Vertical Section Azimuth
data.Description: Azimuth of the vertical section angle relative to local North Reference projected from Vertical Section Origin

data.Name: Remarks
data.Description: Free text comments

data.Name: Gravity Tool Face
data.Description: The angle of the borehole survey instrument within the wellbore measured clockwise relative to up and in the plane perpendicular to the wellbore axis. The high side is the top of the hole perpendicular to the wellbore axis, and the low side is the bottom of the hole.

data.Name: Magnetic Tool Face
data.Description: The magnetic tool face is the direction, in the horizontal plane, that indicates the orientation of the drilling tool face of a deflection tool as an angular measurement from magnetic north.

data.Name: Turn Rate
data.Description: The turn rate refers to the rate at which the direction (azimuth) of the wellbore changes horizontally, typically expressed in degrees per 100 feet (°/100 ft) or degrees per 30 meters (°/30 m).

data.Name: Build Rate
data.Description: The build rate refers to the rate at which the inclination of the wellbore increases over a specified length, typically expressed in degrees per 100 feet (°/100 ft) or degrees per 30 meters (°/30 m).

data.Name: TrajectoryStationType
data.Description: Trajectory station type specific to the station, it can be a notable position in the wellbore.

data.Name: High Side Uncertainty
data.Description: Projection of ellipsoid of uncertainty on high side axis.

data.Name: Lateral Uncertainty
data.Description: Projection of ellipsoid of uncertainty on lateral axis.

data.Name: Along Hole Uncertainty
data.Description: Projection of ellipsoid of uncertainty on along hole axis.

data.Name: Vertical Uncertainty
data.Description: Projection of ellipsoid of uncertainty on vertical axis

data.Name: Variance North North
data.Description: Covariance north north (aka Covariance YY).

data.Name: Variance North East
data.Description: Crossvariance north east (aka Crossvariance YX).

data.Name: Variance East East
data.Description: Covariance east east (aka Covariance XX).

data.Name: Variance North Vertical
data.Description: Crossvariance north vertical (aka Crossvariance XZ) .

data.Name: Variance Vertical Vertical
data.Description: Covariance vertical vertical (aka Covariance ZZ).

data.Name: Variance East Vertical
data.Description: Covariance East Vertical (aka Covariance YZ).

data.Name: Tortuosity
data.Description: Tortuosity refers to the degree of deviation or undulation from the planned well trajectory. It represents the irregularities or oscillations in the wellbore path, which can take various forms such as spiraling, rippling, and hour-glassing. Tortuosity is an important factor because it affects the friction levels, torque, drag, and overall drilling performance.

data.Name: Is Estimated
data.Description: This property indicates if a trajectory station found in the dataset  is estimated (interpolated/extrapolated) and is neither measured nor defined by the user.
